<HEADLINE>
FT  31 MAY 94 / Observer: War games
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
So who did win the war? As the D-day celebrations get under way there seems
to be considerable doubt, according to a poll commissioned by France's Le
Monde newspaper and Ted Turner's CNN TV news network.
Two-thirds of Americans and nearly half the French believe the US did most
to beat the the Nazis. The Germans believe their defeat was jointly
attributable to the then Soviet Union, the US and Britain. Only 18 per cent
of Britons thought that the Americans were the most important factor, whilst
64 per cent of the French believed their Resistance movement was as
important as the Allies in liberating France.
Only thing that everyone agrees on is that the Germans lost.
</TEXT>
