<HEADLINE>
FT  31 MAY 94 / Arts: Today's Television
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER DUNKLEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Today's Life Stories (8.00 BBC1) is one of those episodes that make you
touch wood and mutter 'There but for the grace ..' In the 1960s Alan
Crabtree left Rochdale for South Africa. His career in banking progressed,
he met and married Tish, and they had children. Then he unearthed a fraud at
work and, as seems to happen in these matters, lost his job and his home.
Back in the UK in 1986 the family found themselves in a council flat in
Bethnal Green. Today they are still there, with Alan working as a courier
and Tish bringing in more money from her job in a City optician's.
BBC1 is launching a new drama and, having looked at what is provided
elsewhere, channel controller Alan Yentob and his colleagues have decided
that what we need is a series about a policeman. Yes really. But don't
worry, The Negotiator is no ordinary policeman, gosh no. How about this for
novelty: Charlie King uses unorthodox methods but his superiors overlook it
because he gets results. King is played by Brian Cox who has not played an
idiosyncratic policeman since 'Grushko' (9.35).
</TEXT>
