<HEADLINE>
FT  31 MAY 94 / Management (The Growing Business): Focus on training in
Europe
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Judging by a recent survey of European business attitudes, the UK government
is right to focus on training, the only area to receive significant new
money as a result of last week's competitiveness white paper.
But according to the latest Grant Thornton European business survey* 19 per
cent of UK companies saw no need for training. Only 16 per cent of UK staff
received training in the last year, about the same as the Germans and Dutch,
behind the Austrians and Danes, but more than the Italians or French.
Cost and time were the main reasons training was limited; lack of government
support was seen as the least of the obstacles.
Grant Thornton is running a conference on June 24 in London aimed at
equipping companies with a practical understanding of the European market.
*European Business Survey. Available from Grant Thornton. Tel 071 383 5100.
</TEXT>
