<HEADLINE>
FT  31 MAY 94 / Hosokawa escapes gunshots
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Former Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa yesterday escaped unhurt after a
gunman fired a shot in his direction while he was leaving a Tokyo hotel, AP
reports.
The gunman was wrestled to the floor. Police say they believe he may be a
member of an extremist right-wing group who could have acted out of anger
over Mr Hosokawa's apologies for Japan's actions in the second world war.
