</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MONTREAL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
National Bank, Canada's sixth biggest bank, reported second-quarter net
profit of CDollars 51.9m (USDollars 37.6m), or 27 cents a share, up 27 per
cent from CDollars 40.1m, or 23 cents, a year earlier, writes Robert Gibbens
in Montreal
First-half profit was CDollars 102.5m or 54 cents a share, an increase of 20
per cent from the previous year's CDollars 85.1m or 51 cents.
