<HEADLINE>
FT  30 MAY 94 / Observer: Poor reception
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Concern about the quality of the output of some of Britain's new ITV
franchise holders, highlighted by last week's review by the Independent
Television Commission, reminds Observer of an old definition:
Television is a medium because it is neither rare nor well-done.
