<HEADLINE>
FT  30 MAY 94 / Bullying 'affects 53% of workers'
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
More than half of employees are bullied at work, usually by one of their
managers, a survey showed yesterday.
Researchers from Staffordshire University, who interviewed more than 1,000
workers, found that 53 per cent said they were victims of bullying.
The survey, carried out for a BBC programme, says the most common forms of
bullying are intimidation and regular public humiliation.
