<HEADLINE>
FT  30 MAY 94 / Motorists urged to leave cars at home
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Rush-hour motorists will this week be urged to leave their cars at home for
at least one journey in five during June.
The move is part of a campaign by the Association of Metropolitan
Authorities.
The campaign, which is backed by the Automobile Association, will be
launched tomorrow by Mr Robert Key, the roads minister.
The association said: 'In the same amount of space used by a car, 45 times
as many people can travel by train, 18 times as many by foot, and
seven-and-a-half times as many by bus.'
</TEXT>
