crisis, Reuter reports from Baghdad.
The ruling Revolution Command Council (RCC) said the change was needed
because of the 'unjust (UN) embargo and the need for special effort on
economic issues to protect the living standards of the people'.
Prime Minister Ahmed Hussein Khudayyir was sacked after the Iraqi dinar
plunged to new lows. There were no other big changes in the cabinet, but it
was reported that Mr Saddam would have three deputy prime ministers.
