<HEADLINE>
FT  30 MAY 94 / World News in Brief: European Monetary System
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The order of the EMS grid is unchanged. The Irish punt remains the strongest
currency, but the Dutch guilder and Belgian franc made up ground last week.
The escudo remains bottom, with traders predicting that it might come under
attack this week. Currencies, Page 27
The chart shows the member currencies of the exchange rate mechanism
measured against the weakest currency in the system. Most of the currencies
are permitted to fluctuate within 15 per cent of agreed central rates
against the other members of the mechanism. The exceptions are the D-Mark
and the guilder which move in a 2.25 per cent band.
</TEXT>
