</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Norway's government proposed November 28 as the date of a referendum on
European Union membership yesterday, allowing sceptical Norwegians to decide
after Nordic neighbours Finland and Sweden. The proposal is likely to win
support in parliament, which formally fixes the date. Sweden is to hold its
referendum on November 13 and Finland probably on October 16. Austria, the
fourth country aiming to join from January 1, will hold its vote on June 12.
